To fix the code snippet and prevent Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities, you need to properly sanitize the user input before including it in the response. One common approach to prevent XSS attacks is to escape special characters in the user input. Here's an updated version of the code that implements proper security measures:

